1
00:02:05,345 --> 00:02:06,664
Didn't I tell you

2
00:02:07,745 --> 00:02:09,385
not to talk to her

3
00:02:09,864 --> 00:02:11,585
as long as you're living here?

4
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:14,105
When I locked eyes with Nut earlier,

5
00:02:15,065 --> 00:02:17,385
-my heart was beating really fast.
-What?

6
00:02:18,904 --> 00:02:21,105
You're just like him, Little Prince.

7
00:02:21,184 --> 00:02:23,545
You really care for me.

8
00:02:24,545 --> 00:02:26,785
Now that you know
I'm not related to Neung,

9
00:02:27,545 --> 00:02:29,425
you won't kick me out, will you?

10
00:02:29,904 --> 00:02:31,425
If I wanted to,

11
00:02:31,505 --> 00:02:33,425
I would've left you
at the temple that day.

12
00:02:33,505 --> 00:02:35,464
I'm a bear, not a dog.

13
00:02:36,025 --> 00:02:37,945
Listen. He's just a kid.

14
00:02:38,545 --> 00:02:41,985
Haven't you heard people say
that you should never work with kids?

15
00:02:42,064 --> 00:02:43,665
If you don't trust me…

16
00:02:46,904 --> 00:02:48,904
you could try going out with me.

17
00:03:14,064 --> 00:03:15,665
Everyone, look.

18
00:03:17,025 --> 00:03:20,105
Teddy is acting
more and more like a human.

19
00:03:21,825 --> 00:03:22,784
How?

20
00:03:22,865 --> 00:03:24,904
You seem to have a lot on your mind,

21
00:03:24,985 --> 00:03:27,025
like there's something you want to say

22
00:03:27,504 --> 00:03:28,825
but you won't say it.

23
00:03:28,904 --> 00:03:31,784
You used to say all your thoughts
when you were a teddy bear.

24
00:03:32,945 --> 00:03:35,145
I guess the more time I spend with humans,

25
00:03:36,385 --> 00:03:39,184
the more I know that
there are some things we shouldn't say,

26
00:03:39,745 --> 00:03:41,464
because they can hurt someone.

27
00:03:43,745 --> 00:03:45,665
But some things, I just don't understand,

28
00:03:46,784 --> 00:03:48,224
so I don't know what to say.

29
00:03:48,745 --> 00:03:52,545
If being a human is so hard,
turn back into a teddy bear.

30
00:03:52,624 --> 00:03:53,985
Come back to us.

31
00:03:55,025 --> 00:03:56,545
I'm trying.

32
00:03:57,545 --> 00:04:00,425
I almost found out who gave me to Nut,

33
00:04:01,624 --> 00:04:03,145
but I was still wrong.

34
00:04:03,825 --> 00:04:07,985
Maybe Nut won you
after playing darts at a temple fair?

35
00:04:08,944 --> 00:04:10,265
No!

36
00:04:10,825 --> 00:04:12,865
He said someone important gave me to him.

37
00:04:12,944 --> 00:04:15,105
I must be more important
than a prize at a fair.

38
00:04:15,585 --> 00:04:17,025
Calm down, Tofu.

39
00:04:17,105 --> 00:04:21,144
Look, he gets angry
like a real person now.

40
00:04:21,225 --> 00:04:25,065
-He's kind of similar to Nut.
-He's kind of similar to Nut.

41
00:04:45,985 --> 00:04:47,185
Hey!

42
00:04:49,385 --> 00:04:50,345
Why are you here?

43
00:04:52,545 --> 00:04:54,105
I brought in your laundry.

44
00:04:54,985 --> 00:04:56,465
What should I do next?

45
00:04:57,625 --> 00:04:59,305
You need to go and iron them.

46
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,105
-Iron?
-Yes.

47
00:05:04,824 --> 00:05:06,945
Don't tell me you don't know how to do it.

48
00:05:11,465 --> 00:05:12,704
Listen.

49
00:05:12,785 --> 00:05:14,264
This is linen,

50
00:05:14,785 --> 00:05:15,785
so it needs high heat.

51
00:05:16,264 --> 00:05:18,905
Put the heat on high for linen.

52
00:05:19,785 --> 00:05:21,185
Then start ironing.

53
00:05:23,785 --> 00:05:25,785
Go slowly, see?

54
00:05:27,985 --> 00:05:29,144
Go over the whole thing.

55
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:32,584
That's it.

56
00:05:34,144 --> 00:05:36,264
You try this side.

57
00:05:43,745 --> 00:05:44,745
Slowly.

58
00:05:45,225 --> 00:05:46,345
Yes.

59
00:05:49,105 --> 00:05:51,105
Don't iron over the buttons.

60
00:05:52,305 --> 00:05:53,385
Here.

61
00:05:53,464 --> 00:05:54,584
What you do

62
00:05:54,665 --> 00:05:58,185
is gently push the iron
between the buttons like this.

63
00:05:58,865 --> 00:06:00,185
Slowly.

64
00:06:02,824 --> 00:06:03,745
See?

65
00:06:04,464 --> 00:06:05,385
Yes.

66
00:06:06,425 --> 00:06:07,264
Try it.

67
00:06:09,865 --> 00:06:10,704
Here.

68
00:06:17,225 --> 00:06:19,065
Oh, Tofu.

69
00:06:22,985 --> 00:06:24,185
Here.

70
00:06:24,264 --> 00:06:25,904
Like this, slowly.

71
00:06:36,425 --> 00:06:38,865
Hold the fabric with one hand.

72
00:06:38,945 --> 00:06:39,985
Yes.

73
00:07:23,584 --> 00:07:24,785
Nut, are you hurt?

74
00:07:28,904 --> 00:07:30,225
No,

75
00:07:30,305 --> 00:07:31,385
it's just hot.

76
00:07:33,344 --> 00:07:34,505
Was it hot?

77
00:07:34,584 --> 00:07:36,185
Touch your earlobes.

78
00:07:37,385 --> 00:07:38,425
Is it better?

79
00:07:39,745 --> 00:07:41,105
A little bit.

80
00:07:43,344 --> 00:07:44,665
Hold your earlobes.

81
00:07:44,745 --> 00:07:45,945
What for?

82
00:07:46,024 --> 00:07:47,824
Just do as I say.

83
00:07:48,745 --> 00:07:49,625
No.

84
00:07:51,144 --> 00:07:52,105
-Like this.
-No.

85
00:07:52,185 --> 00:07:53,425
Like this.

86
00:08:25,225 --> 00:08:27,024
It's all right, it's not hot anymore.

87
00:08:30,665 --> 00:08:32,544
Why do I feel so hot?

88
00:08:38,225 --> 00:08:40,784
Is this the sound of my heart or yours?

89
00:08:43,904 --> 00:08:45,745
Get out. You're not good.

90
00:08:47,705 --> 00:08:48,905
I'll do it myself. Go.

91
00:08:50,225 --> 00:08:51,225
Go on.

92
00:09:43,944 --> 00:09:44,985
Beary,

93
00:09:45,064 --> 00:09:47,944
why are you all hot and sweaty?

94
00:09:51,064 --> 00:09:52,465
I was ironing.

95
00:09:52,944 --> 00:09:54,424
Maybe it gave me fever.

96
00:09:54,505 --> 00:09:56,825
Can ironing cause fever?

97
00:09:57,944 --> 00:09:58,785
Right?

98
00:09:58,865 --> 00:10:01,745
Tell me how you feel.

99
00:10:03,865 --> 00:10:05,184
I'm not sure.

100
00:10:07,785 --> 00:10:09,225
I feel hot all over.

101
00:10:11,544 --> 00:10:13,184
There are butterflies in my stomach.

102
00:10:16,304 --> 00:10:17,785
My heart is beating fast too.

103
00:10:18,304 --> 00:10:21,064
You don't sound like you have fever.

104
00:10:21,145 --> 00:10:24,225
Oh, he can't understand you.

105
00:10:24,905 --> 00:10:26,064
Hey, Tofu,

106
00:10:26,145 --> 00:10:27,105
are you sure

107
00:10:27,184 --> 00:10:30,105
that the only thing you did was iron?

108
00:10:31,304 --> 00:10:32,944
It really was.

109
00:10:34,025 --> 00:10:36,145
But while I was ironing,

110
00:10:36,225 --> 00:10:38,145
Nut said he was hot,

111
00:10:39,064 --> 00:10:40,944
so I held his earlobes.

112
00:10:41,865 --> 00:10:43,625
-Held his earlobes?
-Held his earlobes?

113
00:10:43,705 --> 00:10:45,825
Did you hold anything else?

114
00:10:46,785 --> 00:10:47,865
No.

115
00:10:55,705 --> 00:10:59,064
You did just that and then got all hot?

116
00:10:59,905 --> 00:11:02,665
Ha, what do single people know?

117
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:04,544
Little One, tell them.

118
00:11:05,145 --> 00:11:08,824
I think you like Nut, Tofu.

119
00:11:09,345 --> 00:11:11,145
That's why your heart beats fast

120
00:11:11,225 --> 00:11:14,265
and you get butterflies
when you're near him.

121
00:11:16,064 --> 00:11:18,824
It's that feeling you get
when you really like someone.

122
00:11:19,385 --> 00:11:21,225
When you're near them

123
00:11:21,824 --> 00:11:23,505
and lock eyes with them,

124
00:11:23,585 --> 00:11:25,025
your heart starts beating fast.

125
00:11:28,985 --> 00:11:30,865
But I'm just a teddy bear.

126
00:11:31,345 --> 00:11:33,424
How can I like my owner?

127
00:11:33,505 --> 00:11:35,064
Don't forget, Beary,

128
00:11:35,145 --> 00:11:38,304
you're not just a teddy bear anymore.

129
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:41,304
But I have to turn back
into a teddy bear anyway.

130
00:12:06,385 --> 00:12:09,064
I don't know
when I'll turn back into a teddy bear,

131
00:12:10,145 --> 00:12:11,865
but I've decided that

132
00:12:12,585 --> 00:12:13,905
before that day comes,

133
00:12:14,745 --> 00:12:17,225
I'll make the most of my time with Nut.

134
00:12:32,304 --> 00:12:33,585
Nut, are you hurt?

135
00:12:37,665 --> 00:12:38,944
No,

136
00:12:39,025 --> 00:12:40,064
it's just hot.

137
00:12:40,145 --> 00:12:41,585
Hold your earlobes.

138
00:12:41,665 --> 00:12:42,865
What for?

139
00:12:42,944 --> 00:12:44,704
Just do as I say.

140
00:12:45,905 --> 00:12:46,865
-Like this.
-No.

141
00:12:46,944 --> 00:12:48,225
Like this.

142
00:13:00,785 --> 00:13:02,465
Why do I feel so hot?

143
00:13:08,184 --> 00:13:10,625
Is this the sound of my heart or yours?

144
00:13:42,704 --> 00:13:43,665
I'll be off, Mom.

145
00:13:43,745 --> 00:13:45,145
Nut.

146
00:13:48,585 --> 00:13:50,025
It's my first time making it.

147
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:52,145
It might not be very good.

148
00:13:56,745 --> 00:13:58,905
By the way, how's the shirt?

149
00:14:04,345 --> 00:14:05,424
Oh,

150
00:14:05,505 --> 00:14:06,424
where's Mom?

151
00:14:07,905 --> 00:14:08,985
Nut.

152
00:14:11,465 --> 00:14:13,785
I'm sorry, I overslept.

153
00:14:16,985 --> 00:14:18,424
Oh, and your lunch?

154
00:14:19,345 --> 00:14:20,665
I already made it for him.

155
00:14:22,424 --> 00:14:24,424
I'm off to work, Mom.

156
00:14:24,505 --> 00:14:26,025
You should go back to sleep.

157
00:14:29,105 --> 00:14:30,105
Bye.

158
00:14:38,265 --> 00:14:40,505
I can't even wake up
to make lunch for Nut.

159
00:14:42,064 --> 00:14:44,785
How am I supposed to do
other things for him?

160
00:14:45,824 --> 00:14:47,505
Don't worry, Mrs. Na,

161
00:14:47,584 --> 00:14:49,184
anyone can oversleep.

162
00:14:49,824 --> 00:14:52,665
As long as you stay healthy,
Nut will be happy.

163
00:14:58,824 --> 00:15:00,145
Have some apple juice.

164
00:15:01,145 --> 00:15:03,304
Song's father said
it's good for the heart.

165
00:15:04,584 --> 00:15:06,385
I want you to try some.

166
00:15:08,345 --> 00:15:09,304
Thank you.

167
00:15:13,785 --> 00:15:15,505
You're so lovely, Little Prince.

168
00:15:27,544 --> 00:15:28,944
I'm sorry, Mrs. Na.

169
00:15:30,424 --> 00:15:32,385
I made you oversleep.

170
00:15:39,225 --> 00:15:40,665
But if I didn't do this…

171
00:15:42,064 --> 00:15:43,944
Nut wouldn't be happy.

172
00:15:44,785 --> 00:15:46,345
Go on.

173
00:15:50,424 --> 00:15:51,865
What are you making?

174
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,064
Apple juice.

175
00:15:54,145 --> 00:15:55,584
Thank you.

176
00:16:16,865 --> 00:16:18,625
FIRST LOVE

177
00:16:38,145 --> 00:16:39,584
It's my first time making it.

178
00:16:40,064 --> 00:16:41,424
It might not be very good.

179
00:16:56,505 --> 00:16:57,505
Want to try it?

180
00:16:58,424 --> 00:16:59,265
Yuck.

181
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:02,184
Try it. I put a lot of effort into it.

182
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:03,105
Here.

183
00:17:06,224 --> 00:17:07,224
How is it?

184
00:17:08,024 --> 00:17:08,984
Delicious, right?

185
00:17:09,545 --> 00:17:10,464
Hey,

186
00:17:11,305 --> 00:17:12,424
it's great.

187
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:27,065
Iced Americano with no sugar,

188
00:17:27,145 --> 00:17:30,024
but with all my heart,
in exchange for your lunch.

189
00:17:33,905 --> 00:17:36,305
How come your food looks terrible today?

190
00:17:36,385 --> 00:17:37,825
The pork is all burnt.

191
00:17:38,305 --> 00:17:40,065
There's no food for me today then.

192
00:17:40,545 --> 00:17:42,225
I'll throw it out for you.

193
00:17:42,945 --> 00:17:44,024
No,

194
00:17:44,545 --> 00:17:45,825
I can eat it.

195
00:17:57,264 --> 00:17:58,264
Gen,

196
00:18:00,984 --> 00:18:02,865
Nut's taste is so weird.

197
00:18:03,504 --> 00:18:05,865
He gives yummy-looking food
to other people,

198
00:18:05,945 --> 00:18:08,345
but eats burnt pork by himself.

199
00:18:10,705 --> 00:18:13,425
What's so special about that pork?

200
00:18:16,504 --> 00:18:19,585
If he can eat stuff like that,
all is not lost for me.

201
00:18:19,665 --> 00:18:21,024
I have an idea.

202
00:18:23,264 --> 00:18:24,264
You're crazy.

203
00:18:30,504 --> 00:18:31,465
What's up?

204
00:18:33,024 --> 00:18:33,905
What?

205
00:18:33,984 --> 00:18:35,504
You bought an air fryer?

206
00:18:35,585 --> 00:18:36,425
Why?

207
00:18:36,504 --> 00:18:38,185
I'm going to learn to fry pork.

208
00:18:38,865 --> 00:18:41,305
I'll impress Nut with my cooking skills.

209
00:18:42,545 --> 00:18:44,744
You never cease to amaze me.

210
00:18:45,585 --> 00:18:47,744
I'll bring you some to try later.

211
00:18:47,825 --> 00:18:48,825
Bye now.

212
00:18:53,825 --> 00:18:54,825
Oh, Prib.

213
00:18:55,465 --> 00:18:56,625
Oh, Mr. Anik.

214
00:19:00,984 --> 00:19:02,984
Any updates on Tarn's case?

215
00:19:03,065 --> 00:19:05,945
The police
still haven't ruled out anything,

216
00:19:06,024 --> 00:19:09,705
for both the conflict with TRD
and his personal problems.

217
00:19:10,264 --> 00:19:11,984
In his personal life,

218
00:19:12,065 --> 00:19:14,984
I'm certain there's no woman involved.

219
00:19:16,145 --> 00:19:17,744
What makes you think so?

220
00:19:18,504 --> 00:19:21,185
Since he came back to Thailand
two years ago,

221
00:19:21,264 --> 00:19:22,945
he hasn't dated anyone.

222
00:19:23,024 --> 00:19:25,385
He never forgot his first love

223
00:19:25,465 --> 00:19:27,744
and he never got serious with anyone.

224
00:19:28,665 --> 00:19:31,185
I was really touched by that,

225
00:19:31,264 --> 00:19:33,625
so I created a page called

226
00:19:33,705 --> 00:19:35,865
"Once Upon Our Time" to tell his story.

227
00:19:36,345 --> 00:19:40,625
If you check it out,
you might understand him more.

228
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,145
ONCE UPON OUR TIME

229
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:47,984
I didn't know
that Tarn could never love me,

230
00:19:48,065 --> 00:19:50,065
so I made a move on him.

231
00:19:50,705 --> 00:19:53,705
In the end, I failed.

232
00:19:53,784 --> 00:19:56,145
We became good friends instead

233
00:19:56,705 --> 00:19:58,024
and grew a lot closer.

234
00:19:59,744 --> 00:20:03,984
After you've read the page, if you want
to know anything else about Tarn,

235
00:20:04,504 --> 00:20:05,784
you can ask me.

236
00:20:08,504 --> 00:20:09,705
Hey!

237
00:20:11,065 --> 00:20:12,385
You puppy,

238
00:20:12,465 --> 00:20:14,225
you're such a child.

239
00:20:15,945 --> 00:20:17,305
Dad,

240
00:20:17,385 --> 00:20:18,625
are you a BL fanboy?

241
00:20:19,305 --> 00:20:20,984
Are you crazy?

242
00:20:21,065 --> 00:20:22,825
It has to do with my case.

243
00:20:22,905 --> 00:20:25,185
You have cases like this now?

244
00:20:25,264 --> 00:20:26,625
That's pretty trendy.

245
00:20:26,705 --> 00:20:28,784
Of course.

246
00:20:28,865 --> 00:20:30,264
It's Neung's friend's case.

247
00:20:30,825 --> 00:20:32,065
I just realized

248
00:20:32,545 --> 00:20:33,865
that he's not manly.

249
00:20:35,744 --> 00:20:37,065
Not manly?

250
00:20:37,145 --> 00:20:39,145
Just the fact that he's a guy
who likes guys

251
00:20:39,225 --> 00:20:40,585
makes him not manly?

252
00:20:41,465 --> 00:20:43,024
Hey, wait,

253
00:20:44,425 --> 00:20:46,385
what do you think I mean?

254
00:20:47,145 --> 00:20:50,024
What I mean by manly is masculinity.

255
00:20:50,585 --> 00:20:52,305
A person of any gender can be manly.

256
00:20:53,185 --> 00:20:54,784
How did you understand it?

257
00:21:00,145 --> 00:21:01,065
Dad,

258
00:21:01,145 --> 00:21:02,385
keep working.

259
00:21:02,465 --> 00:21:04,345
I'll be the chef tonight.

260
00:21:04,425 --> 00:21:07,065
What do you want,
omelet, fried egg, or steamed egg?

261
00:21:07,865 --> 00:21:08,865
No thanks.

262
00:21:08,945 --> 00:21:10,945
Chef Dad will take care of it.

263
00:21:11,024 --> 00:21:12,625
Go take a shower.

264
00:21:12,705 --> 00:21:14,264
You stink. Go.

265
00:21:14,345 --> 00:21:15,784
Stink? Take that.

266
00:21:17,185 --> 00:21:19,264
Go on, you puppy.

267
00:21:20,225 --> 00:21:21,305
Oh, dear.

268
00:21:34,504 --> 00:21:36,625
Come have some fruit, Mrs. Na.

269
00:21:46,665 --> 00:21:48,145
What are you looking for?

270
00:21:50,784 --> 00:21:52,385
Saen.

271
00:21:54,625 --> 00:21:56,264
I haven't seen him.

272
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:59,024
Did he come home last night?

273
00:22:00,544 --> 00:22:01,984
I think so.

274
00:22:02,585 --> 00:22:04,385
He probably left before you woke up.

275
00:22:04,945 --> 00:22:06,625
Right,

276
00:22:06,705 --> 00:22:08,305
I woke up late today.

277
00:22:10,105 --> 00:22:11,945
I should scold him though.

278
00:22:12,544 --> 00:22:13,825
He could have woken me up.

279
00:22:17,024 --> 00:22:19,544
I don't know
how long he'll be gone this time.

280
00:22:20,185 --> 00:22:22,744
He used to work in a factory
outside Bangkok

281
00:22:22,825 --> 00:22:24,385
and he would come home every week.

282
00:22:24,945 --> 00:22:27,264
Sometimes he would be gone for a few weeks

283
00:22:28,024 --> 00:22:29,865
or even months.

284
00:22:32,705 --> 00:22:34,744
I'm not coming back to Bangkok
this weekend.

285
00:22:34,825 --> 00:22:36,065
Again?

286
00:22:36,825 --> 00:22:38,585
But it's my birthday this Saturday.

287
00:22:39,544 --> 00:22:40,905
Saen?

288
00:22:42,065 --> 00:22:43,065
Saen?

289
00:22:44,185 --> 00:22:45,105
Hello?

290
00:23:03,145 --> 00:23:04,744
Did you get cut off?

291
00:23:05,865 --> 00:23:08,465
Saen is in a meeting.

292
00:23:08,544 --> 00:23:10,665
Do you have a message for him?

293
00:23:10,744 --> 00:23:13,105
Please let it be about work only, though,

294
00:23:13,185 --> 00:23:15,225
because he's working right now.

295
00:23:15,305 --> 00:23:16,865
I'm sorry.

296
00:23:17,425 --> 00:23:19,065
I'll call again later.

297
00:23:25,705 --> 00:23:27,305
Since that year,

298
00:23:28,385 --> 00:23:30,984
he and I haven't celebrated
a birthday together.

299
00:23:34,544 --> 00:23:36,145
That's okay,

300
00:23:36,225 --> 00:23:37,984
we can celebrate together

301
00:23:38,065 --> 00:23:39,345
and make it a huge party.

302
00:23:40,425 --> 00:23:42,425
But I just had my birthday.

303
00:23:43,305 --> 00:23:44,784
But Nut's birthday

304
00:23:44,865 --> 00:23:46,185
is coming up this month.

305
00:23:47,385 --> 00:23:48,625
That's right.

306
00:23:48,705 --> 00:23:49,984
It's only a while

307
00:23:50,065 --> 00:23:51,425
until September 8.

308
00:23:52,665 --> 00:23:54,905
You know his birthday?

309
00:23:58,504 --> 00:24:00,305
He told me once.

310
00:24:04,705 --> 00:24:06,185
Nut is back.

311
00:24:25,625 --> 00:24:26,625
Hi, Mom.

312
00:24:29,784 --> 00:24:30,665
Here.

313
00:24:53,185 --> 00:24:54,665
Didn't you eat my food?

314
00:24:55,544 --> 00:24:57,744
Don't look so sad. Open it up first.

315
00:25:07,825 --> 00:25:10,065
YOURS. MOM'S.

316
00:25:11,145 --> 00:25:12,065
Tofu pudding.

317
00:25:14,345 --> 00:25:15,264
Beans in syrup.

318
00:25:20,544 --> 00:25:22,024
-Fried tofu.
-Yes.

319
00:25:23,024 --> 00:25:24,065
You got these for me?

320
00:25:24,705 --> 00:25:25,905
Can't you read?

321
00:25:27,385 --> 00:25:28,425
KEUNCHAI'S

322
00:25:29,065 --> 00:25:30,825
Keunchai's,

323
00:25:32,585 --> 00:25:33,865
Mom's,

324
00:25:35,825 --> 00:25:37,264
yours.

325
00:25:39,744 --> 00:25:41,024
Mine.

326
00:25:44,665 --> 00:25:45,825
Thank you, Nut.

327
00:25:45,905 --> 00:25:47,625
I'll finish all the tofu pudding.

328
00:25:54,385 --> 00:25:55,304
By the way,

329
00:25:56,065 --> 00:25:57,784
who gave you that pork recipe?

330
00:26:00,065 --> 00:26:01,665
I just followed my gut,

331
00:26:02,504 --> 00:26:03,345
why?

332
00:26:06,865 --> 00:26:07,905
Nothing.

333
00:26:08,465 --> 00:26:11,345
But next time, use less heat.

334
00:26:12,105 --> 00:26:13,625
If I keep eating that,

335
00:26:13,705 --> 00:26:15,024
I'll get cancer.

336
00:26:15,945 --> 00:26:16,984
Okay,

337
00:26:17,065 --> 00:26:19,024
it won't be burnt next time.

338
00:26:20,425 --> 00:26:22,105
I said don't burn it.

339
00:26:22,744 --> 00:26:24,385
Yes, not burnt.

340
00:26:39,264 --> 00:26:41,105
I gathered some more evidence.

341
00:26:42,705 --> 00:26:45,905
Before Tatarn was attacked,

342
00:26:46,544 --> 00:26:49,825
apart from his co-worker,
Mrs. Sajjaree Burarat also called him.

343
00:26:50,385 --> 00:26:52,825
-That's Saen's surname.
-Yes.

344
00:26:52,905 --> 00:26:56,425
She's his wife and Tatarn's aunt.

345
00:26:57,264 --> 00:26:58,385
Isn't that odd?

346
00:26:58,945 --> 00:27:00,065
She lives in Bangkok,

347
00:27:00,145 --> 00:27:01,665
but someone saw her in Chiang Mai

348
00:27:01,744 --> 00:27:03,625
when Tatarn was attacked.

349
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:06,744
Saen never said that his wife
was in Chiang Mai.

350
00:27:06,825 --> 00:27:09,225
It seems like he's hiding something.

351
00:27:10,465 --> 00:27:11,665
Find out

352
00:27:11,744 --> 00:27:14,065
when Sajjaree arrived and left,

353
00:27:14,145 --> 00:27:15,145
and where she went.

354
00:27:15,705 --> 00:27:16,544
Yes, sir.

355
00:27:18,705 --> 00:27:19,705
Please put that away.

356
00:27:20,425 --> 00:27:22,145
Your lieutenant called about the case?

357
00:27:23,544 --> 00:27:24,504
Yes.

358
00:27:25,625 --> 00:27:27,984
We got new evidence
in Neung's friend's case.

359
00:27:28,065 --> 00:27:28,905
So,

360
00:27:29,744 --> 00:27:31,665
do they know who did it?

361
00:27:33,984 --> 00:27:35,225
We still can't say,

362
00:27:36,465 --> 00:27:40,185
but it looks like this wasn't
a normal robbery and attack.

363
00:27:41,024 --> 00:27:43,544
Neung's friend is an activist

364
00:27:43,625 --> 00:27:45,544
and he comes from a wealthy family.

365
00:27:45,625 --> 00:27:46,945
He inherited a lot of money,

366
00:27:47,585 --> 00:27:49,665
so maybe someone is trying to harm him.

367
00:27:50,544 --> 00:27:54,024
The thing I least want to happen

368
00:27:54,744 --> 00:27:56,865
is a family conflict.

369
00:27:58,425 --> 00:27:59,625
That's true, Dad.

370
00:28:00,504 --> 00:28:02,425
If the perpetrator
is someone close to you,

371
00:28:03,225 --> 00:28:04,905
that hurts like nothing else.

372
00:28:09,705 --> 00:28:10,705
Dad,

373
00:28:10,784 --> 00:28:12,665
when do you have to get back to work?

374
00:28:14,065 --> 00:28:15,905
Tomorrow, why?

375
00:28:18,945 --> 00:28:19,905
Nothing.

376
00:28:34,945 --> 00:28:36,544
BRAT

377
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:38,705
Brat.

378
00:28:48,825 --> 00:28:50,865
BRAT

379
00:28:56,544 --> 00:28:58,385
BRAT

380
00:29:13,784 --> 00:29:14,905
BRAT

381
00:29:17,345 --> 00:29:18,705
What is it, you imp?

382
00:29:19,984 --> 00:29:22,504
Man, you're so cold.

383
00:29:24,225 --> 00:29:26,185
Say what you have to say.

384
00:29:26,264 --> 00:29:27,304
I'm about to sleep.

385
00:29:28,825 --> 00:29:30,304
We start filming next week.

386
00:29:31,385 --> 00:29:32,225
So?

387
00:29:32,304 --> 00:29:33,784
Will I get to see you?

388
00:29:35,865 --> 00:29:37,064
I don't think so.

389
00:29:38,064 --> 00:29:39,585
But I want to see you.

390
00:29:41,905 --> 00:29:43,504
Why do you want to see me?

391
00:29:44,225 --> 00:29:45,544
Well,

392
00:29:45,625 --> 00:29:46,865
my dad is busy,

393
00:29:46,945 --> 00:29:50,304
so I want an older relative
to come and give me support.

394
00:29:52,064 --> 00:29:54,905
When did I become your relative?

395
00:29:54,984 --> 00:29:56,705
I keep treating you like an uncle

396
00:29:56,784 --> 00:29:58,585
because I wish you were my family.

397
00:29:58,665 --> 00:29:59,625
Oh,

398
00:29:59,705 --> 00:30:01,385
or should I call you

399
00:30:01,465 --> 00:30:02,665
little brother?

400
00:30:03,145 --> 00:30:05,304
You punk, brat, hoodlum,

401
00:30:05,385 --> 00:30:06,984
disrespectful crazy person!

402
00:30:08,024 --> 00:30:09,665
Now, I can sleep soundly.

403
00:30:10,465 --> 00:30:12,185
You're such a psycho.

404
00:30:12,264 --> 00:30:13,865
See you around.

405
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:15,665
Sweet dreams. Good night.

406
00:30:15,744 --> 00:30:17,585
Kiss, kiss.

407
00:30:19,185 --> 00:30:20,504
Song, you idiot!

408
00:30:43,465 --> 00:30:46,145
I don't know why
I'm so sleepy all the time these days.

409
00:30:46,665 --> 00:30:50,504
If I didn't set three alarms,
I wouldn't have woken up.

410
00:30:51,185 --> 00:30:53,105
I think it's good to rest a lot.

411
00:30:53,185 --> 00:30:54,905
You look much stronger now,

412
00:30:55,504 --> 00:30:57,225
and more energetic during the day too.

413
00:31:02,185 --> 00:31:03,905
-Mom.
-Yes?

414
00:31:04,465 --> 00:31:07,385
We start shooting today,
so you don't need to make me lunch.

415
00:31:07,945 --> 00:31:08,865
I'll eat on the set.

416
00:31:09,905 --> 00:31:10,945
Bye now.

417
00:31:11,865 --> 00:31:13,145
Nut.

418
00:31:43,064 --> 00:31:44,425
Chu.

419
00:31:44,504 --> 00:31:45,945
-Hello.
-Hi.

420
00:31:49,304 --> 00:31:52,225
We went to the market and got you this.

421
00:31:52,304 --> 00:31:53,385
Thank you.

422
00:31:53,465 --> 00:31:54,784
-I'll hold it for you.
-What?

423
00:31:55,504 --> 00:31:57,824
It smells so good.

424
00:31:57,905 --> 00:31:59,665
Hey, listen.

425
00:32:00,425 --> 00:32:03,145
Tofu, do you know where Jan went?

426
00:32:03,225 --> 00:32:04,705
Oh,

427
00:32:04,784 --> 00:32:06,064
is she not home?

428
00:32:07,385 --> 00:32:11,544
No. When I woke up this morning,
I saw her get into a taxi with a suitcase.

429
00:32:13,185 --> 00:32:14,465
She probably…

430
00:32:15,064 --> 00:32:16,824
went to see Mr. Saen in Chiang Mai.

431
00:32:17,385 --> 00:32:21,905
No wonder. They just had a fight.
She must be trying to make it up to him.

432
00:32:21,984 --> 00:32:24,225
Why are you so nosy?

433
00:32:24,784 --> 00:32:27,064
You're unbelievable.

434
00:32:27,145 --> 00:32:28,105
By the way,

435
00:32:28,185 --> 00:32:30,665
how's Na, Tofu?

436
00:32:30,744 --> 00:32:32,585
She hasn't been out to give alms lately.

437
00:32:34,264 --> 00:32:35,625
She's fine.

438
00:32:39,064 --> 00:32:39,905
Tofu,

439
00:32:41,264 --> 00:32:42,744
you know you can talk to me.

440
00:32:44,744 --> 00:32:45,865
Well…

441
00:32:47,504 --> 00:32:48,945
Mrs. Na

442
00:32:49,744 --> 00:32:52,385
hasn't been cooking for Nut.

443
00:32:53,145 --> 00:32:55,425
And she's been feeling sad

444
00:32:55,504 --> 00:32:57,465
and even blaming herself.

445
00:32:57,544 --> 00:32:59,345
She feels worthless.

446
00:32:59,905 --> 00:33:01,945
I understand her, Tofu.

447
00:33:02,024 --> 00:33:04,705
She wants to do things for her son,

448
00:33:04,784 --> 00:33:05,784
like cook for him.

449
00:33:05,865 --> 00:33:08,064
She wants to do
whatever that makes him happy.

450
00:33:08,145 --> 00:33:10,385
But now that he's a grown-up

451
00:33:10,465 --> 00:33:12,345
and he goes to work,

452
00:33:12,425 --> 00:33:14,185
she feels like

453
00:33:14,264 --> 00:33:15,425
she's not useful anymore.

454
00:33:15,504 --> 00:33:16,665
Do you understand?

455
00:33:16,744 --> 00:33:18,465
And Na is always at home.

456
00:33:19,225 --> 00:33:20,544
She never goes out.

457
00:33:20,625 --> 00:33:22,264
So now

458
00:33:22,345 --> 00:33:24,465
that she's not cooking for her son,

459
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:26,784
she probably feels worthless.

460
00:33:28,504 --> 00:33:31,465
And what is it like
to feel you're worth something?

461
00:33:31,544 --> 00:33:32,705
Well,

462
00:33:32,784 --> 00:33:34,824
that has to do with…

463
00:33:34,905 --> 00:33:37,544
I'll let Nhong explain.
He studied engineering.

464
00:33:37,625 --> 00:33:39,945
-Nhong, explain it.
-I went to culinary school.

465
00:33:40,024 --> 00:33:42,385
Come on, explain it.

466
00:33:42,465 --> 00:33:45,665
To feel like you're worth something? Well…

467
00:33:46,625 --> 00:33:47,824
What?

468
00:33:47,905 --> 00:33:51,064
I guess it's when you make
someone else happy.

469
00:33:52,185 --> 00:33:54,705
But it doesn't have to be anything big.

470
00:33:54,784 --> 00:33:56,185
It can be small things,

471
00:33:56,264 --> 00:33:58,865
like giving them support
and making them smile.

472
00:33:58,945 --> 00:34:01,225
And you also feel happy with them.

473
00:34:01,784 --> 00:34:03,705
I guess that's the feeling

474
00:34:03,784 --> 00:34:04,945
of being worth something.

475
00:34:07,984 --> 00:34:09,065
Thank you.

476
00:34:09,145 --> 00:34:11,304
You two are worth a lot to me today.

477
00:34:11,944 --> 00:34:13,625
-Thank you.
-Hey…

478
00:34:16,185 --> 00:34:17,585
-The fried dough?
-What?

479
00:34:17,665 --> 00:34:19,824
Oh, it's so nice. Let me have one more.

480
00:34:20,665 --> 00:34:22,025
I'll be off now.

481
00:34:22,784 --> 00:34:23,985
Why did you eat it?

482
00:34:24,065 --> 00:34:25,344
We bought it for him.

483
00:34:25,985 --> 00:34:27,585
-It's for him.
-It's really good.

484
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:29,985
How can you say that?
Why didn't you give it to him?

485
00:34:30,065 --> 00:34:31,145
Because it's good.

486
00:34:31,225 --> 00:34:33,505
-Try some.
-No.

487
00:34:34,105 --> 00:34:36,864
-It's great.
-You're so bad.

488
00:34:37,824 --> 00:34:39,585
It's really great.

489
00:34:41,065 --> 00:34:42,985
I think I understand now what it means

490
00:34:43,065 --> 00:34:44,944
to feel like you're worth something.

491
00:34:45,545 --> 00:34:47,304
When I was a teddy bear,

492
00:34:47,384 --> 00:34:49,065
I listened to Nut

493
00:34:49,145 --> 00:34:50,585
when he was happy

494
00:34:50,665 --> 00:34:52,105
and when he was sad.

495
00:34:52,185 --> 00:34:53,744
Now that I'm a person,

496
00:34:53,824 --> 00:34:56,665
I feel I'm worth even more

497
00:34:56,744 --> 00:34:58,825
because I don't just listen,

498
00:34:58,904 --> 00:35:01,465
but I can help Nut and Mrs. Na
with a lot of things.

499
00:35:01,545 --> 00:35:02,745
At least,

500
00:35:02,825 --> 00:35:05,345
I don't have to wait to be hugged anymore.

501
00:35:05,424 --> 00:35:08,985
I can hug someone
to make them feel better.

502
00:35:09,665 --> 00:35:11,904
Even though being a human isn't easy,

503
00:35:11,985 --> 00:35:14,904
I'm enjoying it more and more.

504
00:35:50,944 --> 00:35:51,985
Mrs. Na,

505
00:35:53,785 --> 00:35:55,185
shall we make some snacks?

506
00:36:13,465 --> 00:36:15,424
Do you like this location?

507
00:36:16,025 --> 00:36:17,785
The place we booked canceled on us.

508
00:36:18,985 --> 00:36:19,985
Luckily,

509
00:36:20,705 --> 00:36:22,985
my cousin is the deputy director here.

510
00:36:23,065 --> 00:36:24,265
Who?

511
00:36:24,345 --> 00:36:25,944
Joonjuea.

512
00:36:26,025 --> 00:36:29,265
Oh, hi, Pritr.

513
00:36:29,345 --> 00:36:32,665
-I would be in trouble if not for you.
-Yes.

514
00:36:32,745 --> 00:36:34,944
You never come to me
when you're not in trouble.

515
00:36:35,025 --> 00:36:36,265
Hey…

516
00:36:39,745 --> 00:36:40,625
Oh,

517
00:36:41,305 --> 00:36:42,825
aren't you Peeranut?

518
00:36:52,545 --> 00:36:56,505
This school doesn't actually accept
students in the second semester,

519
00:36:56,585 --> 00:36:58,705
but Na is my friend

520
00:36:58,785 --> 00:37:01,585
and Sib has helped me in the past,

521
00:37:01,665 --> 00:37:04,065
so I begged the director to let you in.

522
00:37:04,705 --> 00:37:06,025
Study hard

523
00:37:06,105 --> 00:37:08,105
and don't get me in trouble,

524
00:37:08,185 --> 00:37:09,505
okay?

525
00:37:09,585 --> 00:37:13,745
Don't forget that your parents asked me
to keep an eye on you.

526
00:37:23,545 --> 00:37:25,505
I thought you wouldn't remember me.

527
00:37:25,585 --> 00:37:28,785
It has been around seven to eight years
and you haven't been back once.

528
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:32,825
Did you write the script for this series?

529
00:37:32,904 --> 00:37:34,145
What's it about?

530
00:37:38,625 --> 00:37:40,025
-Hey!
-Hey!

531
00:37:42,625 --> 00:37:45,345
About life in high school?

532
00:37:46,185 --> 00:37:48,625
You didn't use your experience
as material, right?

533
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:50,384
Of course, I did,

534
00:37:51,464 --> 00:37:52,505
but not all of it.

535
00:37:53,864 --> 00:37:56,025
I have both good memories of this place

536
00:37:56,904 --> 00:37:57,864
and not-so-good ones

537
00:38:00,545 --> 00:38:02,505
that I personally want to tell.

538
00:38:04,464 --> 00:38:07,464
But this story isn't just about
the daily lives of kids.

539
00:38:09,185 --> 00:38:11,065
It explores society within a school,

540
00:38:13,025 --> 00:38:14,424
the class system,

541
00:38:15,464 --> 00:38:16,424
power,

542
00:38:17,305 --> 00:38:18,625
and oppression.

543
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:21,705
Interesting.

544
00:38:22,825 --> 00:38:23,745
Does it

545
00:38:24,305 --> 00:38:26,105
also include your love story?

546
00:38:32,225 --> 00:38:33,265
Of course.

547
00:38:33,904 --> 00:38:35,625
And it's not an odd thing anymore.

548
00:38:36,145 --> 00:38:38,025
But it's still not normal.

549
00:38:41,585 --> 00:38:43,025
If for you, normal means

550
00:38:44,464 --> 00:38:46,065
only thinking the way you do,

551
00:38:47,505 --> 00:38:49,384
then half the world would be abnormal.

552
00:38:51,265 --> 00:38:52,625
For me,

553
00:38:53,825 --> 00:38:55,825
everyone is normal.

554
00:38:58,265 --> 00:38:59,864
Just because I'm not like you

555
00:39:00,665 --> 00:39:01,864
or other people

